steps.instruction:
For a more step by step guide go [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2012/02/04/creamy-tomato-soup-can-the-can-%E2%80%93-homemade-is-heavenly)

1. In a large saucepan, heat butter and vegetable oil over medium heat
2. Add onion and saut until golden brown (about 10 minutes)
3. Add tomatoes, basil, thyme and black pepper.
4. Bring the mixture to a summer and cook for 10 minutes
5. In a small bowl, combine the flour and broth, whisking until smooth
6. Add the flour broth mixture to the saucepan, stirring constantly
7. Cover and simmer slowly for 25 minutes, stir occasionally
8. Lower temp to a bare simmer
9. Stir in the baking soda, sugar, milk and salt, stirring constantly
10. Serve hot
